The Herald LONDON. — After 30 years of near misses, some dark days and even mid-table finishes, Liverpool will finally be handed the Premiership trophy at Anfield today, ending the club’s lengthy wait to be champions of England again. Legends were born, and new names added to Anfield folklore, but which of the current crop would now make it into Liverpool’s All-Time XI? BBC Sport has selected a long list of contenders and they include three African stars — Bruce Grobbelaar (Zimbabwe), Sadio Mane (Senegal) and Mohamed Salah (Egypt). <img class="size-full wp-image-466413" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/0501-1-1-BRUCE-GROBELAAR.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/0501-1-1-BRUCE-GROBELAAR.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/0501-1-1-BRUCE-GROBELAAR-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> SYDNEY, AUSTRALIA – JANUARY 07: Bruce Grobbelaar of the Liverpool FC Legends reacts during the match between Liverpool FC Legends and the Australian Legends at ANZ Stadium on January 7, 2016 in Sydney, Australia. (Photo by Zak Kaczmarek/Getty Images) GOALKEEPERS Elisha Scott — Career span at Liverpool: (1912-15 and 1919-34). Appearances/goals: 468/0. Major honours: League title (2) — 1922, 1923. Tommy Lawrence (1957-71). 390/0. League title (2) — 1964, 1966. FA Cup (1) — 1965. Ray Clemence (1967-81). 665/0. League title (5) — 1973, 1976, 1977, 1979, 1980. European Cup (3) — 1977, 1978, 1981. Uefa Cup (2) – 1973, 1976. FA Cup (1) — 1974. League Cup (1) — 1981. Bruce Grobbelaar (1981-94). 628/0. League title (6) — 1982, 1983, 1984, 1986, 1988, 1990. European Cup (1) — 1984. FA Cup (3) — 1986, 1989, 1992. League Cup (3) — 1982, 1983, 1984. Jerzy Dudek (2001-07): 186/0. Champions League (1) — 2005. FA Cup (1) — 2006. League Cup (1) — 2003. Pepe Reina (2005-14). 394/0. FA Cup (1) — 2006. League Cup — (1) — 2012. Alisson (2018-present). 